def: Formed of wood pulp by molds; relating to casts made of woodpulp in molds.
To cover, ornament, line, or stuff with down. [R.] Young.
Striking against; percutient; as, percussive force.
Adapted for swimming or floating; as, natatory organs.

Not refragable; not to be gainsaid or denied; not to be refutedor overthrown; unanswerable; incontestable; undeniable; as, anirrefragable argument; irrefragable evidence.-- Ir*ref"ra*ga*ble*ness, n.-- Ir*ref"ra*ga*bly, adv.
Tending to deviate; devious; as, deviatory motion. [R.] Tully.
A forest; -- used as a termination of names. See Weald.
